<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1438,798,1520]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,336,1416,1442]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[345,557,1417,1442]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimiconformis">
<emphasis box="[345,557,1417,1442]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">D. mimiconformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species endemic to the island of Moloka‘i. It is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,306,1456,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conformis">
<emphasis box="[151,306,1456,1481]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">D. conformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the island of Hawai‘i, but can be easily distinguished by location of collection and a lack of pigmentation in the apical portion of the wing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
